&lt;p&gt;Shape a brighter financial future with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Together with our members, we’re changing the way people think about and interact with personal finance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a next-generation financial services company and national bank using innovative, mobile-first technology to help our millions of members reach their goals. The industry is going through an unprecedented transformation, and we’re at the forefront. We’re proud to come to work every day knowing that what we do has a direct impact on people’s lives, with our core values guiding us every step of the way. &lt;strong&gt;Join us to invest in yourself, your career, and the financial world.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Social Finance, LLC seeks Staff Software Engineer in Seattle, WA:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job Duties: Utilize object-oriented programming languages to build performant and scalable backend applications within a cloud-based microservice architecture. Shape the technical architecture of our products. Own and develop technical solutions for new product requirements. Deliver highly available and scalable services in a production environment. Generate ideas for new initiatives and technologies. Drive operational excellence in our business processes to enhance service quality. Collaborate with business stakeholders, product management, operations, and peer technical teams to deliver impactful products. Mentor team members and foster a learning environment within the team. &lt;strong&gt;Full-time telecommuting is an option.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Requirements: Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering (any field), or a related quantitative discipline and (3) three years of experience in the job offered or in any occupation in related field.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Special Skill Requirements: (1) Java; (2) Kotlin; (3) Microservices; (4) Spring Boot; (5) AWS; (6) Scala; (7) Spring; (8) React; (9) AWS; (10) Distributed Systems; (11) Cloud Computing; (12) API Design &amp;amp; Architecture; (13) Elastic Search; (14) Redis; (15) Relational &amp;amp; Non-Relational DB; (16) Terraform; (17) Python; (18) Kubernetes. Any suitable combination of education, training and/or experience is acceptable. &lt;strong&gt;Full-time telecommuting is an option.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary: $246,600.00 - $271,260.00 per year and standard company benefits.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
